This paper deals with the generalization ability of deep neural networks, which is a fundamental problem in machine learning. The paper proposes a unified framework for analyzing the generalization error of large compressible deep neural networks, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. Specifically, the paper discusses the compression-based bound, which is a technique used in deep learning theory to analyze the generalization error of compressed networks. This technique is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and data structures (cs.DS).
